 Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Hume  .","English: variant of   Holm  .","English: habitational name from Home in Clifton on Teme or in Feckenham (Worcestershire) or from a minor place similarly named, a variant of   Hamm   (from Middle English <i>ham(me)</i>, with rounding of the vowel before the nasal consonant to give <i>hom(me)</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Hume","meanings":["Scottish (Lowlands) and northern English: variant of   Hulme  , with loss of <i>l</i> before the bilabial consonant /m/, as in the vocabulary word <i>calm</i>. See   Holm   and   Home  .","Scottish: habitational name either from the barony of Home or from Hume (or Home) in Berwickshire, from which the barony took its name. The placename derives from Old English <i>hōum</i>, dative plural form of <i>hōh</i> ‘heel, spur of land’.","History: A family of this name (see 2 above) have held the Earldom of Home since 1605."]}]},{"name":"N.N","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a pet form of   Ann   (for the initial <i>N-</i>,  compare  Ned  ). It is now also widely used as a short form of   Nancy ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"N.N Home was born in 1533, in Roman Empire as the daughter of Sir Alexander Hume Lord of Provost Of Edinburgh. She married William Baillie in 1550, in Roman Empire. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1533–":"1533–Surnud","1533–Female":"1533–Surnud","1530–Male":"1530–Surnud","1558–Male":"1558–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1558":"1558","1533":"1533","1530":"1530","1550":"1550","Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Roman Empire":"Roman Empire"},"fi":{"1533–":"1533–Kuollut","1533–Female":"1533–Kuollut","1530–Male":"1530–Kuollut","1558–Male":"1558–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1558":"1558","1533":"1533","1530":"1530","1550":"1550","Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Roman Empire"